history.text: Hi there!
Have you seen this movie before?
I havent seen it in a while however it was a great movie in my eyes such a great story
Hi. Yes, I've seen the movie. Good movie.
i cant beleive it only rated 6.1/10
i thought it was much better
Yeah, although the CinemaScore is A+ so there's that.
very true very true
Sandra Bullock was great of course, but Quinton Aaron also gave a great performance.
yea sandra is typically always good in her movies
Great PR for the Ravens too. Heh.
hahah no kiding im sure they sold all sort of merch
I wonder if John Lee Hancock was the one to read the book and see the potential for a movie.
its possible
did you read the book? i only saw the movie?
curious if they left out any giant parts
No I didn't read the book.
I wonder how SJ was portrayed. That kid was a scene stealer in the movie.
very true very true
curious if his actions were factual
I'm not sure I remember that Leigh Anne was an interior designer. Interesting.
Also Leigh Anne needed better friends.
mhmmm
This movie taught me that career aptitude tests test for protective instincts. Who knew!
hahah i dont recall that being on my tests!
however i wonder if coming from that environment made him to be that great if so i wonder why we dont see more athletes like him
Me neither. I wouldn't do very well protecting the quarterback anyway. lol
I don't know. Even the place he lived, "Hurt Village," sounds rough.
no kidding
i just hoped that this movie would help out people in those situations and really show them that life can get better and there are other options
It's sad that his biological mother couldn't give him what he needed to succeed. I'm sure she loved him. Her circumstances just made it nearly impossible.
yes very true not to say that she wasnt a great mother, just her perdicament made it harder
True. Though not everyone has a Touhy family waiting to help them.
correct they were one of a kind, willing to take on all the responsibility, and to have an outcome like this is very admirable
Yes, they allowed their lives to be upended in order to help someone. Admirable. Though the football connection helped. lol
yea having that stability and sturcture was great
well it has been nice talking with you take care
Thanks. You too.

uid1response.feedback: I hope I gave you what you wanted.
